{
  "text": "CATD stable expressing cells were described previously [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Stable H3 CATD -TAP cell lines were produced by retroviral infection as described [CITATION_4] . Synchronization was achieved as described by [CITATION_5] . For siRNA treatment, 1.5 3 10 5 cells were plated on glass coverslips in a 6 well plate and duplexed siRNAs were introduced into cells using Oligofectamine (Invitrogen, Carlsbad, CA, USA). siRNA-encoding plasmids were cotransfected with RFP-tagged histone H2B (H2B-RFP; [CITATION_6] at a ratio of 20:1 (siRNA:H2B-RFP) using the Effectene transfection reagent (QIAGEN, Valencia, CA, USA). Cells were fixed and processed for immunofluorescence 72 hr after transfection. SNAP labeling was conducted as described previously [CITATION_7] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "21887996",
    "[CITATION_2]": "205286556",
